# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Firebase (frontend – Vite)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. Copy this file to `.env` in the same directory as `package.json` (repo root).
# 2. Fill in values from Firebase Console → Project settings → General → Your apps
#    (pick your Web app, or add one). No quotes around values.
# 3. Restart `npm run dev` — Vite only reads `.env` at startup.
#
# Required for the app to load: API key, Auth domain, Project ID, App ID.
# Optional but recommended: storage bucket, messaging sender ID.
# Only names starting with VITE_ are exposed to the browser bundle.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
